 at the source more carefully, the `label.tag` file is referenced alongside `column_link`, suggesting it's a similar widget component for adding labeled output to columns. The inline expanding panel detail is a specific UI implementation that could matter for developers, but the core behavior—showing alternate formatting in narrow mode—is already captured in the knowledge file. I need to apply the rules about what constitutes decision-necessary information—warnings about incorrect behavior and best practices matter, but descriptive details about UI implementation don't necessarily rise to that level. The critical constraint about incompatibility with autospan/rowspan is already captured, so the omission of the inline expanding panel description is genuinely minor. I'm confident the knowledge file is largely accurate with just that one small gap in the `additional` attribute for s2. The property and file path names don't match the V4 check criteria for PascalCase classes, annotations, or exceptions, so I'll set this aside as well. That leaves just the one minor omission I found.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15994,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":15994,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90958bcb-9105-451e-b271-e6b38fcc93db","uuid":"214c2ff2-8bf1-419a-90af-b3bba8ff7699"}
